description:
Are the messages of Revelation 18 still relevant to God’s people? Who is Babylon? Have we forgotten what we once taught? Who will give the Loud Cry if the church is fast asleep? 

The headlines show that we are standing on the very brink of eternity – massive charismatic revivals are springing up under the leadership of popular preachers, the wall between church and state is being swiftly demolished, the pope has breached the gaps between world religions including Islam, and daily headlines trumpet world-changing events that are happening with lightning speed.

Have we fallen asleep? We believe that the Advent movement arose to prepare those living in the last days for Christ’s coming. As Seventh-day Adventists we should understand the symbols and messages of Revelation if we are to be involved in the Loud Cry. But many of us seem to have forgotten the truths of Revelation that we once taught from our pulpits and understood.
